ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[It is imperative that the epidemiology of zoonotic diseases such as CCHF be understood at the national and regional/provincial levels, given the large number of livestock in the country, and its importance to the economy and livelihood of rural communities. Furthermore, it is important that hospital staff be educated to consider CCHF as a possible disease agent, since they are at high risk of contracting the disease, especially in hospitals with limited resources. - Mod.UBA

